1
00:00:07,458 --> 00:00:10,333
♪

2
00:00:18,916 --> 00:00:21,791
[man singing in Japanese]

3
00:01:37,416 --> 00:01:41,125
♪

4
00:01:47,750 --> 00:01:49,625
♪

5
00:01:51,833 --> 00:01:52,708
[gasps]

6
00:01:54,916 --> 00:01:55,875
[gasps]

7
00:01:57,833 --> 00:02:00,416
[SAIKI] Oh, no. I already regret
getting that kid's balloon.

8
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:02,000
[giggles]

9
00:02:02,083 --> 00:02:04,833
Hey, mister, are you
Cyborg Cider-man Number 2?

10
00:02:04,916 --> 00:02:06,041
Because I think you are.

11
00:02:06,125 --> 00:02:07,208
[SAIKI]
Sorry, but I am not

12
00:02:07,291 --> 00:02:09,000
Cyborg Cider-man Number 2.

13
00:02:09,083 --> 00:02:10,875
[YUUTA]
Your secret's safe with me,

14
00:02:10,958 --> 00:02:11,875
Cyborg Cider-man Number Two.

15
00:02:11,958 --> 00:02:13,750
[SAIKI]
Wrong. I'm not a cyborg,

16
00:02:13,833 --> 00:02:16,000
a Cider-man, or a Number 2,
or any other number.

17
00:02:16,083 --> 00:02:18,541
But I just saw you do the
Soda Jump to save my balloon.

18
00:02:18,625 --> 00:02:20,250
It's too late
to try to hide it now.

19
00:02:20,333 --> 00:02:22,583
[SAIKI] I'm not a superhero.
I'm a high school student.

20
00:02:22,666 --> 00:02:24,833
Can I have your autograph?
Here.

21
00:02:24,916 --> 00:02:26,083
[gasps]

22
00:02:26,166 --> 00:02:28,000
[SAIKI]
I don't have time for this.

23
00:02:28,083 --> 00:02:29,958
[wailing]

24
00:02:31,333 --> 00:02:32,625
[YUUTA]
Whoa! Thank you!

25
00:02:32,708 --> 00:02:34,333
I'll never wash this bag
again.

26
00:02:34,416 --> 00:02:36,041
[SAIKI]
He can't be more than 5.

27
00:02:36,125 --> 00:02:37,666
Where's his mom? Is he lost?

28
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:39,958
So can you please do
the Soda Jump again?

29
00:02:40,041 --> 00:02:41,875
[SAIKI] I can't believe
this is a real hero.

30
00:02:41,958 --> 00:02:43,875
Is there
a Cyborg Cider-man Number 1?

31
00:02:43,958 --> 00:02:45,833
I always drink Energy Cider
to support you.

32
00:02:45,916 --> 00:02:49,208
[SAIKI] His entire comic's
just an ad for some gross drink.

33
00:02:49,291 --> 00:02:51,875
So it's just sleazy marketing
tactics to rip off kids.

34
00:02:51,958 --> 00:02:53,333
[YUUTA]
Come on. Do the Soda Jump.

35
00:02:53,416 --> 00:02:54,708
The carbonation from the soda

36
00:02:54,791 --> 00:02:56,375
shooting out of the bottom
of your feet

37
00:02:56,458 --> 00:02:58,375
is what makes you jump
so high in the air, right?

38
00:02:58,458 --> 00:02:59,958
[SAIKI]
That's a lot of carbonation.

39
00:03:00,041 --> 00:03:01,583
[YUUTA]
Jump! Do it! Do it!

40
00:03:01,666 --> 00:03:02,958
[grunting]

41
00:03:03,041 --> 00:03:04,083
Whoa!

42
00:03:04,166 --> 00:03:05,583
[SAIKI]
Idiot. Psychokinesis.

43
00:03:05,666 --> 00:03:07,250
[MAN]
Whoa! What?

44
00:03:07,333 --> 00:03:09,416
That was close.

45
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:11,291
That was the Soda Air Cannon.

46
00:03:11,375 --> 00:03:13,166
The Soda Air Cannon is real!

47
00:03:13,250 --> 00:03:14,791
I know that move.

48
00:03:14,875 --> 00:03:16,958
It's like you use
the amazing power of carbonation

49
00:03:17,041 --> 00:03:19,375
from the soda out of your hands
to blow away your enemies.

50
00:03:19,458 --> 00:03:21,333
[SAIKI] Soda shoots
out of his hands and feet?

51
00:03:21,416 --> 00:03:23,208
That's not a great power
for a cyborg.

52
00:03:23,291 --> 00:03:24,791
We're raising
a generation of kids

53
00:03:24,875 --> 00:03:26,625
with unrealistic
soda expectations.

54
00:03:26,708 --> 00:03:28,916
[YUUTA] I know everything
there is to know about soda

55
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,666
and Cyborg Cider-man
Number 2.

56
00:03:30,750 --> 00:03:32,916
[SAIKI] Have they even replaced
his blood with soda?

57
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:36,416
I know you're Cyborg Cider-man
Number 2. I'm sure of it.

58
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:38,416
Cyborg Cider-man Number 2,
I love you so much!

59
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:39,875
[SAIKI]
Does he really need to say

60
00:03:39,958 --> 00:03:41,416
that stupid full name
every time?

61
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:43,458
It's so annoying.
Good motivation to find

62
00:03:43,541 --> 00:03:45,291
the kid's parents ASAP,
though.

63
00:03:45,375 --> 00:03:46,875
Hey, a policeman.
That was easy.

64
00:03:46,958 --> 00:03:48,125
This little boy lost?

65
00:03:48,208 --> 00:03:49,541
[Yuuta laughing]
Suspicious.

66
00:03:49,625 --> 00:03:51,250
Why does this kid
love this teen so much?

67
00:03:51,333 --> 00:03:53,208
[SAIKI] Isn't that better
than the opposite?

68
00:03:53,291 --> 00:03:55,875
[OFFICER] Thirteen years on the
job and my gut says this is bad.

69
00:03:55,958 --> 00:03:58,125
[SAIKI] Find a new job.
Anyway, the kid's all yours.

70
00:03:58,208 --> 00:03:59,666
I'm out of here.

71
00:03:59,750 --> 00:04:01,750
All right, son, are you friends
with that big kid?

72
00:04:01,833 --> 00:04:04,625
Yes, sir. He's a superhero
with a secret identity.

73
00:04:04,708 --> 00:04:06,333
You should've seen him
shoot a car.

74
00:04:06,416 --> 00:04:09,291
Hey hold it right there!

75
00:04:11,291 --> 00:04:12,916
Where'd the policeman go?

76
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,166
[SAIKI]
Oh, just a little

77
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:15,875
soda-infused
obstruction of justice.

78
00:04:15,958 --> 00:04:17,541
This kid's parents
could be anywhere.

79
00:04:17,625 --> 00:04:20,083
My telepathy hasn't picked up
their voices,

80
00:04:20,166 --> 00:04:22,208
so they're outside
my 200-meter radius.

81
00:04:22,291 --> 00:04:23,708
[exhales audibly]
Question.

82
00:04:23,791 --> 00:04:25,708
Is your archenemy
Baron Cola really strong?

83
00:04:25,791 --> 00:04:27,250
[SAIKI]
Yeah, he's strong.

84
00:04:27,333 --> 00:04:29,166
You'd think being lost
would scare this kid.

85
00:04:29,250 --> 00:04:31,500
[YUUTA] It's getting dark,
Cyborg Cider-man Number 2,

86
00:04:31,583 --> 00:04:32,625
so it's time to go home.

87
00:04:32,708 --> 00:04:33,625
Right, Mommy?

88
00:04:33,708 --> 00:04:35,625
Hmm. What?

89
00:04:35,708 --> 00:04:38,583
My mommy's gone and I'm scared!
[SAIKI] You just realized this?

90
00:04:38,666 --> 00:04:39,916
[wails]

91
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,500
Somebody help me!
My mommy got lost!

92
00:04:41,583 --> 00:04:42,916
[SAIKI]
No, you got lost.

93
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,916
I thought she was right
behind me all this time,

94
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:46,500
but it turns out
it was just a balloon.

95
00:04:46,583 --> 00:04:48,458
[SAIKI] Are 5-year-olds
always this stupid?

96
00:04:48,541 --> 00:04:49,875
Oh, Cyborg Cider-man
Number 2,

97
00:04:49,958 --> 00:04:51,291
please go find my mommy
for me.

98
00:04:51,375 --> 00:04:53,250
[SAIKI]
I don't think I have a choice.

99
00:04:53,333 --> 00:04:54,666
What do you want? What--?

100
00:04:54,750 --> 00:04:57,250
[SAIKI]
Get on. I'll do the Soda Jump.

101
00:04:57,333 --> 00:05:00,458
Whoa! I'm flying
with a superhero! Best day ever!

102
00:05:00,541 --> 00:05:02,500
[SAIKI] Quiet down,
you'll draw attention.

103
00:05:02,583 --> 00:05:03,666
[YUUTA]
Mommy!

104
00:05:03,750 --> 00:05:05,500
Oh, Yuuta.

105
00:05:05,583 --> 00:05:07,708
Where have you been?
I was about to call the police.

106
00:05:07,791 --> 00:05:09,208
Heh. Don't worry, Mommy.

107
00:05:09,291 --> 00:05:11,125
Cyborg Cider-man Number 2
rescued me,

108
00:05:11,208 --> 00:05:12,708
and then we flew here.
Right?

109
00:05:12,791 --> 00:05:14,958
[Yuuta gasps]
[MOM] Honey, I don't see anyone.

110
00:05:15,041 --> 00:05:16,833
I think this hero
was in your imagination.

111
00:05:16,916 --> 00:05:18,791
[SAIKI] Cyborg Cider-man
Number Two's fate

112
00:05:18,875 --> 00:05:20,333
is to remain hidden
in the shadows.

113
00:05:20,416 --> 00:05:21,666
[YUUTA]
I did, I really met him.

114
00:05:21,750 --> 00:05:24,166
I even got his autogra--
It's gone.

115
00:05:24,250 --> 00:05:26,583
[SAIKI] Forget this happened.
It was all a dream.

116
00:05:26,666 --> 00:05:28,833
[MOM] I'll chalk all this up
to you being stressed out

117
00:05:28,916 --> 00:05:30,833
over moving into the new house.
[gate squeaks]

118
00:05:30,916 --> 00:05:32,291
Oh, hello there, neighbor.

119
00:05:32,375 --> 00:05:34,541
We're the Iridatsu Family.

120
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:36,041
We just moved in next door
today.

121
00:05:36,125 --> 00:05:38,291
Aah!
Cyborg Cider-man Number 2.

122
00:05:38,375 --> 00:05:40,250
It's him. I told you, Mom.
I told you he's real.

123
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:41,875
[SAIKI]
He's my new neighbor?

124
00:05:41,958 --> 00:05:45,250
♪

125
00:05:46,958 --> 00:05:49,125
[KUNIHARA]
Aah! Look at the time!

126
00:05:49,208 --> 00:05:50,958
I just woke up
and I'm already late for work.

127
00:05:51,041 --> 00:05:53,250
How did this happen?
[SAIKI] Summer vacation's here,

128
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:55,541
but now I have to wake up
to this guy every day.

129
00:05:55,625 --> 00:05:57,250
Aah! Help me out, Dr. Kuu.

130
00:05:57,333 --> 00:05:59,000
Make that blue box
that teleports me to--

131
00:05:59,083 --> 00:06:00,166
[SAIKI]
Not a chance.

132
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:01,583
No, Kusuo,

133
00:06:01,666 --> 00:06:02,583
don't make me beg you.

134
00:06:02,666 --> 00:06:03,875
[screaming]

135
00:06:03,958 --> 00:06:05,416
[SAIKI] You're being
too dramatic.

136
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:07,166
Don't use me,
use your own two feet.

137
00:06:07,250 --> 00:06:09,791
Take me and I'll bring you back
a coffee jelly when I come home.

138
00:06:09,875 --> 00:06:11,458
[SAIKI] We're here.
[KUNIHARA] What?

139
00:06:11,541 --> 00:06:12,708
We're already on the roof

140
00:06:12,791 --> 00:06:14,458
of my office?
Thank you, Kusuo.

141
00:06:14,541 --> 00:06:16,916
Now my boss'll slap me just
four times instead of five.

142
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,583
[SAIKI]
That's practically the same.

143
00:06:18,666 --> 00:06:20,875
Since you're here, why
don't you check out the office?

144
00:06:20,958 --> 00:06:22,708
[SAIKI] Yeah, I don't even know
what you do.

145
00:06:22,791 --> 00:06:24,958
You switch jobs so often,
it's hard to keep straight.

146
00:06:25,041 --> 00:06:26,416
You clean shoes or something?

147
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:28,250
[KUNIHARU] I work for
a publishing company

148
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:30,000
called Shuensha.

149
00:06:30,083 --> 00:06:32,041
[SAIKI]
Shueisha? They're huge.

150
00:06:32,125 --> 00:06:34,000
One of the leading publishers
in Japan,

151
00:06:34,083 --> 00:06:36,333
and a magnet for the best
and brightest in the industry.

152
00:06:36,416 --> 00:06:39,333
No, you misheard me.
Not Shueisha. Shuensha.

153
00:06:39,416 --> 00:06:40,416
[SAIKI]
Shuensha?

154
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:41,708
You're not the first person

155
00:06:41,791 --> 00:06:43,291
to mix us up.
It's a real problem.

156
00:06:43,375 --> 00:06:45,333
[SAIKI] Seems intentional
more than anything.

157
00:06:45,416 --> 00:06:47,375
They're written
totally different. Look. Huh?

158
00:06:47,458 --> 00:06:49,000
[SAIKI]
You know <i>shuen</i> means death?

159
00:06:49,083 --> 00:06:51,208
You might be excited to learn
that your old man's job

160
00:06:51,291 --> 00:06:52,916
is to edit manga.
[SAIKI] Manga?

161
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,708
[KUNIHARA] Here.
Editorial department

162
00:06:54,791 --> 00:06:56,875
for <i>The Weekly Shonen Cognac.</i>
[SAIKI] Come again?

163
00:06:56,958 --> 00:06:58,125
What's with the blank stare?

164
00:06:58,208 --> 00:07:00,000
Don't tell me
you've never heard

165
00:07:00,083 --> 00:07:02,458
of <i>Weekly Shonen Cognac</i> manga.
[SAIKI] Never heard of it.

166
00:07:02,541 --> 00:07:04,708
<i>Jump Magazine, Sunday</i>
<i>Champion, and Cognac,</i> right?

167
00:07:04,791 --> 00:07:06,125
[SAIKI]
I know those first four.

168
00:07:06,208 --> 00:07:07,250
[Kuniharu whimpers]

169
00:07:07,333 --> 00:07:09,000
[ONIMATSU] About time.
[yelps]

170
00:07:09,083 --> 00:07:11,333
Did you get here late because
you like getting slapped?

171
00:07:11,416 --> 00:07:13,166
[whimpering]
[ONIMATSU] Who's that?

172
00:07:13,250 --> 00:07:14,708
This is my boy, Kusuo.

173
00:07:14,791 --> 00:07:16,791
Huge fan of the magazine,
collects the whole run.

174
00:07:16,875 --> 00:07:19,000
For weeks he's been begging me
to bring him by

175
00:07:19,083 --> 00:07:20,583
so he can meet
the great chief editor.

176
00:07:20,666 --> 00:07:22,500
Well, I never wanna disappoint
a fan.

177
00:07:22,583 --> 00:07:24,333
I'm Onimatsu,
the great chief editor.

178
00:07:24,416 --> 00:07:26,666
You're addicted to Cognac.
[SAIKI] Dad just wanted me

179
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:28,208
as cover to get his boss
off his back.

180
00:07:28,291 --> 00:07:29,916
[ONIMATSU]
Give your boy the full tour.

181
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,500
Just make sure
you get your work done.

182
00:07:31,583 --> 00:07:32,500
[door closes]

183
00:07:32,583 --> 00:07:33,625
All right, thanks to you,

184
00:07:33,708 --> 00:07:35,000
I got off with no slaps
at all.

185
00:07:35,083 --> 00:07:36,708
One coffee jelly
isn't enough for this.

186
00:07:36,791 --> 00:07:38,750
[KUNIHARU] This is where
the magic gets edited.

187
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:40,333
[SAIKI]
This place looks pretty sad.

188
00:07:40,416 --> 00:07:42,458
Seeing how manga
gets made could be interesting.

189
00:07:42,541 --> 00:07:44,541
[EDITOR] How much longer
do you expect me to wait?

190
00:07:44,625 --> 00:07:46,375
A deadline isn't a suggestion!

191
00:07:46,458 --> 00:07:47,541
What? More time?

192
00:07:47,625 --> 00:07:48,875
[KUNIHARU]
Being a writer

193
00:07:48,958 --> 00:07:50,583
can be difficult
and time-consuming.

194
00:07:50,666 --> 00:07:52,833
So every morning, we editors
call them up to check in,

195
00:07:52,916 --> 00:07:54,625
chat, and offer
friendly encouragement.

196
00:07:54,708 --> 00:07:56,583
I will beat this script
out of you, if I have to.

197
00:07:56,666 --> 00:07:57,875
[SAIKI]
A lovely group of men.

198
00:07:57,958 --> 00:07:59,375
Check out
our most recent issue.

199
00:07:59,458 --> 00:08:01,083
You at least recognize
the logo, right?

200
00:08:01,166 --> 00:08:02,708
[SAIKI] No.
[KUNIHARU] Here.

201
00:08:02,791 --> 00:08:05,000
You don't want it?
But this is our top character,

202
00:08:05,083 --> 00:08:06,708
The Ever Optimistic
Santarou.

203
00:08:06,791 --> 00:08:09,208
In fact, every issue's loaded
with great manga.

204
00:08:09,291 --> 00:08:11,125
[SAIKI] The editors
need to edit the titles.

205
00:08:11,208 --> 00:08:12,875
[KUNIHARU]
They're good. Read it.

206
00:08:12,958 --> 00:08:14,291
You won't even open it?

207
00:08:14,375 --> 00:08:15,958
[EDITOR]
Mr. Saiki, you got a visitor.

208
00:08:16,041 --> 00:08:17,291
I almost forgot.
I'm scheduled

209
00:08:17,375 --> 00:08:18,708
to hear a new pitch
this morning.

210
00:08:18,791 --> 00:08:20,250
Don't cause any trouble.

211
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:21,750
[SAIKI]
Unbelievable.

212
00:08:21,833 --> 00:08:24,041
My dad's a manga editor.
How weird is that?

213
00:08:24,125 --> 00:08:25,875
I've caught him
reading manga,

214
00:08:25,958 --> 00:08:28,375
but at home he never mentions
or even thinks about his work.

215
00:08:28,458 --> 00:08:30,250
[KUNIHARU]
Aw. My Kurumi is such a cutie.

216
00:08:30,333 --> 00:08:32,416
She's washing dishes.
[SAIKI] Though, to be fair,

217
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:34,000
the only thing he
thinks about is Mom.

218
00:08:34,083 --> 00:08:36,708
I wonder how his meeting's
going. Better check in.

219
00:08:36,791 --> 00:08:37,875
♪

220
00:08:37,958 --> 00:08:39,833
You've addressed
all of my notes.

221
00:08:39,916 --> 00:08:42,041
I like how you've cut way back
on the dialogue

222
00:08:42,125 --> 00:08:44,333
and are letting the art
and layout create the tension.

223
00:08:44,416 --> 00:08:46,083
But the characters
could use some work.

224
00:08:46,166 --> 00:08:48,375
[SAIKI] He actually sounds
like he's good at his job.

225
00:08:48,458 --> 00:08:50,625
Have you thought about
making the main guy a psychic?

226
00:08:50,708 --> 00:08:51,875
[WRITER] What?
[SAIKI] Hey.

227
00:08:51,958 --> 00:08:52,875
But it's supposed to be

228
00:08:52,958 --> 00:08:54,291
a realistic sports drama.

229
00:08:54,375 --> 00:08:56,208
[KUNIHARU] Yeah.
Maybe add some dry wit too.

230
00:08:56,291 --> 00:08:58,208
I'm sorry, but your notes
don't make any sense.

231
00:08:58,291 --> 00:09:01,083
[KUNIHARU] Look, to be safe,
bring me something like <i>Naruto.</i>

232
00:09:01,166 --> 00:09:02,666
[WRITER]
I can't do that.

233
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,750
Sorry about that.
[SAIKI] Don't apologize to me.

234
00:09:04,833 --> 00:09:06,708
Apologize to that writer.
[cell phone rings]

235
00:09:06,791 --> 00:09:07,958
Sorry. It's another one.

236
00:09:08,041 --> 00:09:09,458
Yeah, Saiki here.

237
00:09:09,541 --> 00:09:11,125
What's up? Oh, that?
Yeah, you got it.

238
00:09:11,208 --> 00:09:12,791
[SAIKI]
I've never seen him like this.

239
00:09:12,875 --> 00:09:14,791
Thanks for touching base.
[SAIKI] Well.

240
00:09:14,875 --> 00:09:16,541
You don't have to go home, son.

241
00:09:16,625 --> 00:09:18,125
[SAIKI]
I don't wanna get in your way.

242
00:09:18,208 --> 00:09:20,291
This job's not as fancy
as it sounds.

243
00:09:20,375 --> 00:09:22,083
And let me tell you,
when it's crunch time,

244
00:09:22,166 --> 00:09:24,416
there's no superhero
coming to save us.

245
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:26,666
But every time I see
those finished manga pages

246
00:09:26,750 --> 00:09:29,000
printed with a story the
writer poured his heart into,

247
00:09:29,083 --> 00:09:31,208
it makes all the stress
and boss slapping worth it.

248
00:09:31,291 --> 00:09:32,916
[SAIKI]
Hmph. Thanks for working hard

249
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,041
to provide for us, Dad.

250
00:09:35,125 --> 00:09:37,250
Ha-ha-ha. Bye, son.

251
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:39,708
Right. I've gotta send
yesterday's finished pages

252
00:09:39,791 --> 00:09:42,041
to the printer-- Ugh.

253
00:09:42,125 --> 00:09:44,208
Kusuo! Kusuo, help me!

254
00:09:44,291 --> 00:09:46,958
[SAIKI] Nope.
You already said no heroes.

255
00:09:47,041 --> 00:09:51,416
[man sings in Japanese]

256
00:09:52,458 --> 00:09:55,500
♪

257
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:59,041
[SAIKI]
Summer break's the best.

258
00:09:59,125 --> 00:10:00,500
Once I'm done
with my homework,

259
00:10:00,583 --> 00:10:02,333
which I can knock out
in a few hours,

260
00:10:02,416 --> 00:10:04,375
I can just hang out and read,
and no one will care.

261
00:10:04,458 --> 00:10:07,666
Best of all, today no one's even
home. When you're a psychic,

262
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:09,875
this is pretty much the
only time in the entire year

263
00:10:09,958 --> 00:10:11,500
when you can relax.
[doorbell rings]

264
00:10:11,583 --> 00:10:13,041
And now Nendou's here
to ruin that.

265
00:10:13,125 --> 00:10:14,583
Wait. It's even worse.

266
00:10:14,666 --> 00:10:17,083
Hello and good morning,
Cyborg Cider-man Number 2.

267
00:10:17,166 --> 00:10:19,000
[SAIKI] Right.
Mom mentioned this earlier.

268
00:10:19,083 --> 00:10:20,958
That neighbor boy,
Yuuta's home alone today.

269
00:10:21,041 --> 00:10:23,458
so be nice and spend some time
with him, if he stops by, okay?

270
00:10:23,541 --> 00:10:25,083
[SAIKI]
But being nice is so hard.

271
00:10:25,166 --> 00:10:28,166
Whoa! So this is Cyborg
Cider-man Number 2's

272
00:10:28,250 --> 00:10:29,416
secret base.

273
00:10:30,541 --> 00:10:31,875
Hold on. Why's there

274
00:10:31,958 --> 00:10:33,583
no soda coming out.
[SAIKI] It's a sink.

275
00:10:33,666 --> 00:10:34,916
What? According to the comics,

276
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,625
Cyborg Cider-man Number 2
uses soda

277
00:10:36,708 --> 00:10:38,666
everywhere in his life
where we would use water.

278
00:10:38,750 --> 00:10:40,458
[SAIKI]
Wouldn't he get sick of that?

279
00:10:40,541 --> 00:10:42,875
[YUUTA] At least tell me the
water in your toilet is soda.

280
00:10:42,958 --> 00:10:45,250
The bubbles clean stains.
[SAIKI] That's convenient.

281
00:10:45,333 --> 00:10:47,666
Oh, well. Who cares about
all of the soda in your home

282
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:49,333
when I've got
the latest Blu-ray of you

283
00:10:49,416 --> 00:10:50,875
kicking bad guy booty.

284
00:10:50,958 --> 00:10:52,500
Watch it with me.
[SAIKI] Uh...

285
00:10:52,583 --> 00:10:54,625
Awesome!
Watching Cyborg Cider-man

286
00:10:54,708 --> 00:10:56,541
while sitting
next to Cyborg Cider-man

287
00:10:56,625 --> 00:10:59,125
is like eating ramen while
watching a TV show about it.

288
00:10:59,208 --> 00:11:02,375
[SAIKI] That only makes sense
if you don't think about it.

289
00:11:02,458 --> 00:11:03,833
Whoa!

290
00:11:03,916 --> 00:11:05,500
♪

291
00:11:05,583 --> 00:11:07,541
[NARRATOR]
<i>Cyborg Cider-man.</i>

292
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:09,166
<i>Number 2!</i>
Whoa!

293
00:11:09,250 --> 00:11:10,750
Whoa! Whoa!

294
00:11:10,833 --> 00:11:12,916
[SAIKI] Can't you just
sit quietly and enjoy it?

295
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:16,000
[NARRATOR] <i>Episode 10:</i>
<i>The Lemonade Fiend Appears.</i>

296
00:11:16,083 --> 00:11:17,666
[MAN] <i>The Lemonade Fiend</i>
<i>has appeared!</i>

297
00:11:19,208 --> 00:11:20,708
<i>Aah! It burns, it burns!</i>

298
00:11:20,791 --> 00:11:22,125
<i>You jerk!</i>

299
00:11:22,208 --> 00:11:24,000
<i>Ow! My eyes!</i>
[Lemonade laughing]

300
00:11:24,083 --> 00:11:26,291
<i>Whenever we hit him, he just</i>
<i>squirts lemon juice on us.</i>

301
00:11:26,375 --> 00:11:28,750
<i>He's taking over the world!</i>
[SAIKI] A giant lemon?

302
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:30,666
[both gasp]
[MAN] <i>An empty soda bottle.</i>

303
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:32,833
[CIDER-MAN] <i>Hold it</i>
<i>right there, Lemonade Fiend.</i>

304
00:11:32,916 --> 00:11:34,541
<i>Huh? That voice!</i>

305
00:11:34,625 --> 00:11:38,041
<i>Cyborg Cider-man Number 2</i>
<i>fizzes onto the scene!</i>

306
00:11:38,125 --> 00:11:39,666
Whoa!
[SAIKI] Keep it down.

307
00:11:39,750 --> 00:11:41,458
What do you think'll happen?
Will he win?

308
00:11:41,541 --> 00:11:43,083
[SAIKI] If you stay quiet,
he'll win.

309
00:11:43,166 --> 00:11:45,041
<i>Take this, Lemonade!</i>
<i>Soda Punch!</i>

310
00:11:45,125 --> 00:11:47,291
<i>Wait! Don't punch him!</i>
<i>The impact will spray the city</i>

311
00:11:47,375 --> 00:11:48,500
<i>with lemon juice!</i>

312
00:11:48,583 --> 00:11:49,916
<i>Fizz!</i>
[WOMAN] <i>Oh, no!</i>

313
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,541
<i>He's become more</i>
<i>citrus sourness</i>

314
00:11:51,625 --> 00:11:53,791
<i>than man now!</i>
[WOMAN] <i>Earth is doomed!</i>

315
00:11:53,875 --> 00:11:55,500
<i>Wait, hold on!</i>
[Woman gasps]

316
00:11:55,583 --> 00:11:57,583
[MAN] <i>It's having no effect</i>
<i>on Cider-man!</i>

317
00:11:57,666 --> 00:11:59,375
<i>He looks like</i>
<i>that was nothing to him!</i>

318
00:11:59,458 --> 00:12:01,583
<i>That was nothing to me!</i>
[MAN] <i>My God, he just said it!</i>

319
00:12:01,666 --> 00:12:03,250
[LEMONADE]
<i>No! Impossible!</i>

320
00:12:03,333 --> 00:12:06,666
<i>Heh. You just made lemon soda.</i>
<i>What? Lemon soda?</i>

321
00:12:06,750 --> 00:12:08,958
[CIDER-MAN] <i>That's right.</i>
<i>When you add lemon to soda,</i>

322
00:12:09,041 --> 00:12:11,500
<i>you're adding a sour kick to</i>
<i>that great, natural sweetness.</i>

323
00:12:11,583 --> 00:12:13,375
<i>Not to mention a whole lot</i>
<i>of vitamin C.</i>

324
00:12:13,458 --> 00:12:15,250
<i>It's the perfect</i>
<i>summer thirst quencher!</i>

325
00:12:15,333 --> 00:12:18,041
<i>You see, your lemon juice</i>
<i>has actually powered me up!</i>

326
00:12:18,125 --> 00:12:19,291
<i>Ha! Take this!</i>

327
00:12:19,375 --> 00:12:21,750
<i>Lemon Soda Attack!</i>

328
00:12:21,833 --> 00:12:24,083
<i>Find it wherever food</i>
<i>and drinks are sold!</i>

329
00:12:24,166 --> 00:12:27,208
<i>Aah! It's only 148 yen</i>
<i>after tax?</i>

330
00:12:27,291 --> 00:12:28,666
[SAIKI]
That thing was just an ad.

331
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:29,875
Yeah! Cider-man won!

332
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:31,375
[SAIKI]
Could it get more blatant?

333
00:12:31,458 --> 00:12:32,708
That was fun
sitting next to you

334
00:12:32,791 --> 00:12:34,125
and watching you beat
Lemonade.

335
00:12:34,208 --> 00:12:35,916
Now take me to the store
to get a lemon soda.

336
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,500
[SAIKI]
You lost the real battle.

337
00:12:37,583 --> 00:12:39,083
Show me
your Lemon Soda Attack now,

338
00:12:39,166 --> 00:12:41,500
Cyborg Cider-man Number 2
or get me a lemon soda.

339
00:12:41,583 --> 00:12:43,208
[SAIKI] You'll get nothing
and like it.

340
00:12:43,291 --> 00:12:44,625
[MAN] Here you go.
Lemon soda!

341
00:12:44,708 --> 00:12:46,833
Hey. Good thing I bought
three of these, huh?

342
00:12:46,916 --> 00:12:48,250
Now my buddy's kid bro
gets one.

343
00:12:50,375 --> 00:12:51,583
[SAIKI]
Lemon Soda Attack!

344
00:12:51,666 --> 00:12:52,750
[NENDOU]
Lemon what?

345
00:12:52,833 --> 00:12:54,458
Why'd you hit me?

346
00:12:54,541 --> 00:12:56,666
[SAIKI] He's not my brother,
and get out of my house.

347
00:12:56,750 --> 00:12:59,500
No fighting in the Soda base!
Are you okay, mister?

348
00:12:59,583 --> 00:13:02,458
Yeah. Thanks for asking me,
little boy.

349
00:13:02,541 --> 00:13:04,208
[whimpering]

350
00:13:04,291 --> 00:13:06,041
[Yuuta screaming]
[NENDOU] What's wrong?

351
00:13:06,125 --> 00:13:07,500
[SAIKI]
Your face is terrifying.

352
00:13:07,583 --> 00:13:08,791
This big guy is your archenemy,

353
00:13:08,875 --> 00:13:10,208
Baron Cola!
[SAIKI] Baron Cola?

354
00:13:10,291 --> 00:13:11,791
[LEMONADE]
Baron Cola,

355
00:13:11,875 --> 00:13:14,125
my humblest apologies.
Next time--

356
00:13:14,208 --> 00:13:15,875
[BARON COLA]
There will be no next time.

357
00:13:15,958 --> 00:13:17,958
But I will gladly add
your lemon juice

358
00:13:18,041 --> 00:13:19,708
to my Bad Cola power.

359
00:13:19,791 --> 00:13:21,541
When life gives you lemons
after all.

360
00:13:21,625 --> 00:13:23,000
[SAIKI] That's totally Nendou.

361
00:13:23,083 --> 00:13:24,666
Oh.
[SAIKI] You got a point, kid.

362
00:13:24,750 --> 00:13:26,875
Don't let him pickle me,
Cyborg Cider-man Number 2.

363
00:13:26,958 --> 00:13:28,666
[SAIKI]
I can't believe the resemblance.

364
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:30,333
What's going on?
[NENDOU] Baron Cola.

365
00:13:30,416 --> 00:13:31,958
[SAIKI]
You know this show? Figures.

366
00:13:32,041 --> 00:13:34,541
Baron Cola's my favorite
comic book super villain.

367
00:13:34,625 --> 00:13:36,333
He was even the inspiration
for me growing

368
00:13:36,416 --> 00:13:38,416
this thick mustache.
[SAIKI] Thick?

369
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:40,375
[NENDOU] I get it.
That's why you're scared.

370
00:13:40,458 --> 00:13:42,500
Look. There's nothing
to be afraid of.

371
00:13:42,583 --> 00:13:44,291
See? I'm not scary, right?

372
00:13:44,375 --> 00:13:45,833
[whimpering]

373
00:13:45,916 --> 00:13:47,583
Aah!
He's gonna pickle me in cola!

374
00:13:47,666 --> 00:13:49,666
[SAIKI] Oh, man.
I can see how if you're a kid,

375
00:13:49,750 --> 00:13:51,125
he's pretty traumatizing.

376
00:13:51,208 --> 00:13:53,125
I can't see too well
when making this face.

377
00:13:53,208 --> 00:13:55,166
How's the little kid?
[SAIKI] Soda, get out!

378
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:56,958
[Nendou screaming]

379
00:13:57,041 --> 00:13:59,791
♪

380
00:14:03,583 --> 00:14:06,583
[SAIKI] I see. I was wondering
what all the commotion was.

381
00:14:06,666 --> 00:14:08,708
Turns out it's some kind
of summer festival.

382
00:14:08,791 --> 00:14:10,125
Usually crowds bug me,

383
00:14:10,208 --> 00:14:11,875
but I'm actually okay
with these things.

384
00:14:11,958 --> 00:14:13,375
[boy cheers]
[bell ringing]

385
00:14:13,458 --> 00:14:14,916
[VENDOR]
Congratulations!

386
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:17,000
You just won a generic knock-off
of a popular toy!

387
00:14:17,083 --> 00:14:19,166
[BOY] Yay!
[SAIKI] My parents used to take

388
00:14:19,250 --> 00:14:20,583
me to festivals all the time.

389
00:14:20,666 --> 00:14:22,583
I was obsessed with winning
this one prize,

390
00:14:22,666 --> 00:14:23,875
but I never got it.

391
00:14:23,958 --> 00:14:25,375
Sorry, kid.
Better luck next time.

392
00:14:25,458 --> 00:14:27,625
[SAIKI] Years later,
it still bothers me.

393
00:14:27,708 --> 00:14:30,125
But all in all, I have
good memories of the fair.

394
00:14:30,208 --> 00:14:32,166
Man, what a big crowd.
[indistinct chattering]

395
00:14:32,250 --> 00:14:34,750
My telepathy's gonna be
pretty much useless here.

396
00:14:34,833 --> 00:14:36,666
Gotta keep my eyes open,
make sure I don't run

397
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:38,666
into anyone I know.
[NENDOU] For the last time!

398
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:40,666
There's no octopus
in these takoyaki.

399
00:14:40,750 --> 00:14:42,916
I'm returning them for a refund!
[MAN 1] You can't...

400
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:46,041
[SAIKI] That was close.
Time for an alternate route.

401
00:14:46,125 --> 00:14:49,083
Twenty-two caliber. Not a bad
weapon for hunting small game.

402
00:14:49,166 --> 00:14:50,625
Hair trigger's always nice,

403
00:14:50,708 --> 00:14:52,833
and I like having
that bolt-action for durability.

404
00:14:52,916 --> 00:14:54,416
[MAN 2]
It's just a cork gun.

405
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:56,666
[KAIDOU] Ready, fire!
[MAN 2] Sorry, you missed.

406
00:14:56,750 --> 00:14:58,708
[ALL] Heave-ho!
[MAN 3] Everyone out of the way!

407
00:14:58,791 --> 00:15:01,541
[MAN 4] The festival mikoshi
is coming through!

408
00:15:01,625 --> 00:15:05,958
[ALL]
Heave-ho! Heave-ho! Heave-ho!

409
00:15:06,041 --> 00:15:07,708
[SAIKI]
That's a sore sight for eyes.

410
00:15:07,791 --> 00:15:10,041
I should go before I start
hating festivals.

411
00:15:10,125 --> 00:15:11,541
I'll get one of these
for the road.

412
00:15:11,625 --> 00:15:13,166
[MAN 5]
That'll be 300 yen.

413
00:15:13,250 --> 00:15:16,458
[SAIKI]
Hmm. My wallet's gone.

414
00:15:16,541 --> 00:15:18,541
[MAN 5] Something wrong?
[SAIKI] Did I drop it?

415
00:15:18,625 --> 00:15:20,291
No, I don't make mistakes
like that.

416
00:15:20,375 --> 00:15:22,166
And it couldn't have been
a thief.

417
00:15:22,250 --> 00:15:24,583
[MAN 6] Easy to pick pockets
when there's so many people.

418
00:15:24,666 --> 00:15:26,333
[MAN 7]
I could go for another hot dog.

419
00:15:26,416 --> 00:15:28,875
[SAIKI] With so many people,
I can't tell who's saying what.

420
00:15:28,958 --> 00:15:30,583
[TAKAHASHI] It's gone!
[YOKOTA] What?

421
00:15:30,666 --> 00:15:32,166
My wallet!
Someone must've taken it!

422
00:15:32,250 --> 00:15:34,000
That's a drag, dude.
How much cash was in it?

423
00:15:34,083 --> 00:15:35,583
On the way over,
I remember you saying

424
00:15:35,666 --> 00:15:38,000
you put every last penny
you earned this summer in there.

425
00:15:38,083 --> 00:15:40,208
[SAIKI] Sounds like Takahashi
got pick-pocketed.

426
00:15:40,291 --> 00:15:41,791
Like I say,
you gotta pay attention

427
00:15:41,875 --> 00:15:43,500
at all times in crowds
like this.

428
00:15:43,583 --> 00:15:44,791
What a joke.

429
00:15:44,875 --> 00:15:46,625
Pick. Pick-pocketed?

430
00:15:46,708 --> 00:15:47,875
I can't deny it anymore.

431
00:15:47,958 --> 00:15:49,291
That must be what happened
to me.

432
00:15:49,375 --> 00:15:50,708
I got ripped off.

433
00:15:50,791 --> 00:15:53,250
I, an all-seeing psychic,
got ripped off.

434
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:54,541
[babbling]

435
00:15:54,625 --> 00:15:56,291
[MURATA]
Whoa! Takahashi just broke.

436
00:15:56,375 --> 00:15:58,083
[SAIKI] I can't laugh.
I feel the same way.

437
00:15:58,166 --> 00:15:59,916
[both babbling]

438
00:16:01,833 --> 00:16:04,208
[MAN 1] Cool, fireworks!
[WOMAN] Didn't know it was time.

439
00:16:04,291 --> 00:16:05,541
[MAN 2]
Not for another hour.

440
00:16:05,625 --> 00:16:07,791
[SAIKI]
I've never felt so humiliated.

441
00:16:07,875 --> 00:16:09,666
[laughs]

442
00:16:09,750 --> 00:16:11,666
Festivals sure are fun,
aren't they?

443
00:16:11,750 --> 00:16:13,250
Well, guess what,
Mr. Pickpocket,

444
00:16:13,333 --> 00:16:14,958
now I'll make you pay...
with interest.

445
00:16:15,041 --> 00:16:17,125
Only problem
is it's gonna be hard

446
00:16:17,208 --> 00:16:19,833
to find him with telepathy alone
in a crowd this big.

447
00:16:19,916 --> 00:16:21,125
I'll have to lure him out.

448
00:16:21,208 --> 00:16:23,666
This should work.

449
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:25,125
[man chuckling]

450
00:16:25,208 --> 00:16:26,875
[MAN] One night's work
and I made enough

451
00:16:26,958 --> 00:16:28,333
to carry me through summer.

452
00:16:28,416 --> 00:16:30,750
Thanks for donating
to my personal charity.

453
00:16:30,833 --> 00:16:32,500
Huh, my backpack's heavy.

454
00:16:32,583 --> 00:16:33,958
[screaming]

455
00:16:34,041 --> 00:16:35,000
[grunts]

456
00:16:35,083 --> 00:16:36,208
[MAN 1]
What the hell?

457
00:16:36,291 --> 00:16:37,625
[MAN 2]
A motorcycle fell on him!

458
00:16:37,708 --> 00:16:39,166
What the hell happened?

459
00:16:39,250 --> 00:16:41,208
Get this thing off me.

460
00:16:41,291 --> 00:16:42,833
[MAN 3]
Hey, you left your bike.

461
00:16:44,375 --> 00:16:46,125
Ow! Stupid tree!

462
00:16:46,208 --> 00:16:47,666
[screams]

463
00:16:47,750 --> 00:16:49,666
[SAIKI] Did you enjoy
the little trade I made?

464
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:51,291
I found
an abandoned motorcycle,

465
00:16:51,375 --> 00:16:52,750
and after fixing it up,
I realized

466
00:16:52,833 --> 00:16:54,208
it was worth the same
as my wallet,

467
00:16:54,291 --> 00:16:55,625
so I switched the two.

468
00:16:55,708 --> 00:16:57,416
All I had to do then
was use my clairvoyance

469
00:16:57,500 --> 00:16:59,500
to find a big commotion,
which led me right to you.

470
00:16:59,583 --> 00:17:01,125
[whimpering]
All you need to know

471
00:17:01,208 --> 00:17:03,375
is that you should never steal
a psychic's wallet.

472
00:17:03,458 --> 00:17:05,500
Because there are
grave consequences.

473
00:17:05,583 --> 00:17:07,875
♪

474
00:17:07,958 --> 00:17:10,250
[man screaming]

475
00:17:12,166 --> 00:17:13,166
[sighs]

476
00:17:13,250 --> 00:17:15,000
This night's a total loss.

477
00:17:15,083 --> 00:17:16,375
Wait.
What?

478
00:17:16,458 --> 00:17:18,208
[MAN 1] I found my wallet.
[MAN 2] Really?

479
00:17:18,291 --> 00:17:21,083
[SAIKI] Three to go. I could've
had the police handle this part,

480
00:17:21,166 --> 00:17:22,875
but it would've taken longer
for everyone

481
00:17:22,958 --> 00:17:24,291
to get their wallets back.

482
00:17:24,375 --> 00:17:26,125
And that would ruin
the fun of the festival.

483
00:17:26,208 --> 00:17:28,875
Besides, with psychometry, I can
easily find the owners myself.

484
00:17:28,958 --> 00:17:30,708
So it's no big deal. Hmm?

485
00:17:30,791 --> 00:17:32,166
My wallet's gone!

486
00:17:32,250 --> 00:17:33,958
Dark Reunion stole it!
[SAIKI] Is this it?

487
00:17:34,041 --> 00:17:35,541
Huh? What?

488
00:17:35,625 --> 00:17:37,791
[SAIKI] Everyone I know
looks like an idiot tonight.

489
00:17:37,875 --> 00:17:38,791
Well, two more.

490
00:17:38,875 --> 00:17:40,458
My wallet! It's gone!

491
00:17:40,541 --> 00:17:42,666
It was here a moment ago!
[SAIKI] In your loincloth?

492
00:17:42,750 --> 00:17:44,500
Aah!
[SAIKI] Now whose is this?

493
00:17:44,583 --> 00:17:46,541
Hey, buddy,
is that my missing wallet?

494
00:17:46,625 --> 00:17:48,000
Big surprise.

495
00:17:48,083 --> 00:17:50,000
Whoa.
Saiki's at the festival too.

496
00:17:50,083 --> 00:17:51,541
Saiki. Nendou.
What's up, guys?

497
00:17:51,625 --> 00:17:53,583
[SAIKI] What a pain.
They found me, after all.

498
00:17:53,666 --> 00:17:56,958
Hmm. Which reminds me, I didn't
find Takahashi's wallet.

499
00:17:57,041 --> 00:17:58,958
[babbling]

500
00:17:59,041 --> 00:18:02,000
[MURATA]
Let's just go home.

501
00:18:02,083 --> 00:18:06,541
[man sings in Japanese]

502
00:18:07,541 --> 00:18:10,958
♪

503
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:14,208
[NARRATOR]
Here we find a beautiful girl,

504
00:18:14,291 --> 00:18:16,291
this one with much on her mind.
[Teruhashi sighs]

505
00:18:16,375 --> 00:18:18,250
[TERUHASHI] Why can't I
get him out of my head?

506
00:18:18,333 --> 00:18:20,666
[NARRATOR]
Kokomi Teruhashi, 16 years old.

507
00:18:20,750 --> 00:18:22,375
[TERUHASHI]
Is it true love? No!

508
00:18:22,458 --> 00:18:24,333
I just can't believe
that a boring guy like him

509
00:18:24,416 --> 00:18:26,625
is all "no, wow!" around me
instead of "oh, wow!"

510
00:18:26,708 --> 00:18:28,708
I swear, I will make
Kunio Saiki fall for me,

511
00:18:28,791 --> 00:18:30,458
no matter what it takes.

512
00:18:30,541 --> 00:18:33,416
[NARRATOR] Elsewhere.
[YUMEHARA] What am I gonna do?

513
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:35,666
[NARRATOR] We find another,
not as attractive girl,

514
00:18:35,750 --> 00:18:37,875
with much on her mind.
[YUMEHARA] How come I haven't

515
00:18:37,958 --> 00:18:39,083
been in any episodes lately?

516
00:18:39,166 --> 00:18:40,625
[NARRATOR]
Chiyo Yumehara, age 16.

517
00:18:40,708 --> 00:18:42,125
[YUMEHARA]
What I'm worried about

518
00:18:42,208 --> 00:18:43,458
is my relationship
with Saiki!

519
00:18:43,541 --> 00:18:45,166
Whenever I wanna get close
to him,

520
00:18:45,250 --> 00:18:47,625
it's like there's some invisible
force pulling us apart.

521
00:18:47,708 --> 00:18:49,666
[NARRATOR] And so right on cue.
[both gasp]

522
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:50,916
Kokomi?

523
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:52,708
Yumehara?
[NARRATOR] They meet.

524
00:18:52,791 --> 00:18:55,250
[YUMEHARA] Is this the first
time we've met outside school?

525
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:56,958
You know,
I think you're right.

526
00:18:57,041 --> 00:18:59,291
I wish I knew before that
you liked to come to this place.

527
00:18:59,375 --> 00:19:00,625
Yeah, it's quiet.

528
00:19:00,708 --> 00:19:02,125
Makes a good place
to study or read.

529
00:19:02,208 --> 00:19:04,833
[YUMEHARA]
Neat.

530
00:19:04,916 --> 00:19:07,250
[TERUHASHI] This is awkward.
If we never talk at school,

531
00:19:07,333 --> 00:19:08,958
what are we supposed
to talk about here?

532
00:19:09,041 --> 00:19:10,666
[YUMEHARA] Do we know
each other enough

533
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:12,625
for me to just call her Kokomi
like that?

534
00:19:12,708 --> 00:19:14,125
Hey.
So...

535
00:19:14,208 --> 00:19:15,666
♪

536
00:19:15,750 --> 00:19:16,666
[both sigh]

537
00:19:18,375 --> 00:19:21,000
So excited for that
school field trip coming up?

538
00:19:21,083 --> 00:19:23,333
Yeah, I'm super excited.
I love Okinawa.

539
00:19:23,416 --> 00:19:25,666
Mm. It's gonna be so fun.

540
00:19:25,750 --> 00:19:27,916
[YUMEHARA]
A three-day trip with Saiki.

541
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,333
Heaven.

542
00:19:29,416 --> 00:19:31,125
[TERUHASHI]
A three-day trip with Saiki.

543
00:19:31,208 --> 00:19:33,541
The only thing hotter than
these Okinawa beaches is you.

544
00:19:33,625 --> 00:19:34,833
[NARRATOR]
Love fantasy.

545
00:19:34,916 --> 00:19:37,041
You're more worthy
of an "oh, wow"

546
00:19:37,125 --> 00:19:38,541
than the Okinawan sea.

547
00:19:38,625 --> 00:19:40,166
[YUMEHARA &amp; TERUHASHI]
The dream.

548
00:19:40,250 --> 00:19:41,166
[both gasp]

549
00:19:41,250 --> 00:19:42,375
Were you saying something?

550
00:19:42,458 --> 00:19:43,750
What? No, nothing at all.

551
00:19:43,833 --> 00:19:45,333
What about you?
Uh, no.

552
00:19:45,416 --> 00:19:47,958
I wasn't thinking
about any boys at school.

553
00:19:49,458 --> 00:19:51,041
Kokomi, do you have a crush
on anyone?

554
00:19:51,125 --> 00:19:52,333
[gasps]

555
00:19:52,416 --> 00:19:54,500
What? You do?
[TERUHASHI] No! No, no.

556
00:19:54,583 --> 00:19:56,583
I just wasn't expecting
such a private question.

557
00:19:56,666 --> 00:19:58,333
There's no way
you'd have a crush.

558
00:19:58,416 --> 00:20:01,416
Someone as pretty as you can
have any guy she wants, anytime.

559
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:03,125
Well, thank you,
but what about you?

560
00:20:03,208 --> 00:20:04,333
Do you have a crush?

561
00:20:04,416 --> 00:20:05,916
Yeah. Heh.

562
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:08,416
[TERUHASHI] Really, who?
[YUMEHARA] Promise not to tell?

563
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:10,500
[TERUHASHI] Is he in our class?
[YUMEHARA] Yeah.

564
00:20:10,583 --> 00:20:12,125
Heh. Oh, that's nice.

565
00:20:12,208 --> 00:20:13,791
[TERUHASHI]
It can't be Saiki, can it?

566
00:20:13,875 --> 00:20:15,541
I'm dying to know.
[YUMEHARA] My psych--

567
00:20:15,625 --> 00:20:17,541
[TERUHASHI] What'd you say?
Well, my psycho ex

568
00:20:17,625 --> 00:20:18,958
is finally out of the picture.

569
00:20:19,041 --> 00:20:20,708
[TERUHASHI]
Aah! Ha, ha. Psycho. Got it.

570
00:20:20,791 --> 00:20:22,125
[YUMEHARA]
My crush is actually

571
00:20:22,208 --> 00:20:23,583
someone I liked
before I met my ex.

572
00:20:23,666 --> 00:20:25,125
[TERUHASHI]
Oh, wow. I had no idea

573
00:20:25,208 --> 00:20:27,541
Yumehara had
so much experience with boys.

574
00:20:27,625 --> 00:20:30,041
Maybe I should just ask her
for advice.

575
00:20:30,125 --> 00:20:31,541
[TERUHASHI]
Um, well, the truth is

576
00:20:31,625 --> 00:20:33,083
there is someone in our class
I like.

577
00:20:33,166 --> 00:20:34,791
[blowing]

578
00:20:34,875 --> 00:20:37,250
Tell me! Tell me! Tell me!
Is it a French guy? No, Russian!

579
00:20:37,333 --> 00:20:39,875
[TERUHASHI] Bring down
that volume. You're drooling.

580
00:20:39,958 --> 00:20:41,291
[YUMEHARA]
All right, I'm calm.

581
00:20:41,375 --> 00:20:42,916
Now, please give me a name?

582
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:45,000
You're surrounded by
so many guys, I have no clue.

583
00:20:45,083 --> 00:20:46,833
I'm not always around boys.

584
00:20:46,916 --> 00:20:48,916
The last time I did that
was New Year's Day

585
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,375
when me, Hairo
and the others

586
00:20:50,458 --> 00:20:52,833
went to Saiki's house
to celebrate.

587
00:20:52,916 --> 00:20:54,416
[YUMEHARA]
Oh, Saiki, huh?

588
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:56,500
[YUMEHARA] I wasn't expecting
to hear that name

589
00:20:56,583 --> 00:20:57,750
come out of Kokomi's mouth.

590
00:20:57,833 --> 00:20:59,208
[TERUHASHI]
What was that about?

591
00:20:59,291 --> 00:21:00,916
Was she reacting
to hearing Saiki?

592
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:03,250
[YUMEHARA] Could it be that
[TERUHASHI] Does that mean

593
00:21:03,333 --> 00:21:06,041
[YUMEHARA] Kokomi's crush...
[TERUHASHI] Yumehara's crush...

594
00:21:06,125 --> 00:21:07,833
[YUMEHARA &amp; TERUHASHI]
is Saiki?

595
00:21:07,916 --> 00:21:10,333
[NARRATOR] Little do the girls
know the man of their dreams

596
00:21:10,416 --> 00:21:12,416
sits next to them.
[KAIDOU] What's wrong, Saiki?

597
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:14,458
You look sick. Oh, no,
is Dark Reunion behind me?

598
00:21:14,541 --> 00:21:15,708
[SAIKI]
What do I do?

599
00:21:15,791 --> 00:21:17,041
If they end up
fighting over me,

600
00:21:17,125 --> 00:21:18,541
they'll be in my life
all the time,

601
00:21:18,625 --> 00:21:19,916
scheming to win
my affection.

602
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,458
That'll be worse
than having to deal

603
00:21:21,541 --> 00:21:22,708
with Kaidou and Nendou.

604
00:21:22,791 --> 00:21:24,291
The girls are this close
to realizing

605
00:21:24,375 --> 00:21:25,916
that each of them
has a crush on me.

606
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:28,125
I have to nip this in the bud
before feelings get hurt

607
00:21:28,208 --> 00:21:29,625
and my life gets ruined.

608
00:21:29,708 --> 00:21:31,666
Hey, sorry, I blew my wrapper
over there.

609
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:32,833
Oh, wow, it's Teruhashi.

610
00:21:32,916 --> 00:21:34,875
What? Nendou?
[SAIKI] Idiot.

611
00:21:34,958 --> 00:21:37,041
Aah! Oh, no.
Did he hear us?

612
00:21:37,125 --> 00:21:38,625
Kokomi.
She's blushing.

613
00:21:38,708 --> 00:21:40,708
I was right.
There's no doubt.

614
00:21:40,791 --> 00:21:43,291
[YUMEHARA] Kokomi likes...
[TERUHASHI] Yumehara likes...

615
00:21:43,375 --> 00:21:44,625
[YUMEHARA &amp; TERUHASHI]
Saiki.

616
00:21:44,708 --> 00:21:46,166
[SAIKI]
Don't jump to conclusions.

617
00:21:46,250 --> 00:21:47,458
Huh?
[gasps]

618
00:21:47,541 --> 00:21:49,250
[KAIDOU] My bad.
My deepest apologies.

619
00:21:49,333 --> 00:21:51,250
[TERUHASHI]
She's blushing more than before.

620
00:21:51,333 --> 00:21:53,000
Which means
the boy Yumehara likes is...

621
00:21:53,083 --> 00:21:55,166
[SAIKI] Your turn, Teruhashi.
Oh, sorry.

622
00:21:55,250 --> 00:21:56,791
Wow! She's so red.

623
00:21:56,875 --> 00:21:58,625
Means the guy she likes
isn't Saiki. It's--

624
00:21:58,708 --> 00:22:01,500
[SAIKI] I'm warming the girls'
faces using pyrokinesis.

625
00:22:03,166 --> 00:22:05,083
[SAIKI] That was close.
[TERUHASHI] It's cute

626
00:22:05,166 --> 00:22:06,833
that Yumehara's secret crush
is Kaidou.

627
00:22:06,916 --> 00:22:08,416
[YUMEHARA]
I never would've guessed

628
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:09,833
Kokomi has the hots for Nendou.

629
00:22:09,916 --> 00:22:11,791
[SAIKI] I may have just
made things even worse.

630
00:22:12,916 --> 00:22:17,000
♪

631
00:22:21,666 --> 00:22:25,541
[woman singing in Japanese]

632
00:22:57,208 --> 00:22:59,083
[all singing in Japanese]

633
00:23:42,333 --> 00:23:45,083
[SAIKI] Okay, folks, one
last time, so we're all clear.

634
00:23:45,166 --> 00:23:48,083
I'm not a cyborg, a Cider-Man
or a Number 2 anything.

635
00:23:48,166 --> 00:23:50,083
Next time, on
<i>The Disastrous Life of Saiki K.</i>

636
00:23:50,166 --> 00:23:51,625
The big school trip
that everyone's

637
00:23:51,708 --> 00:23:53,583
been looking forward to,
except the writers.

638
00:23:53,666 --> 00:23:55,333
There are so many characters
on this show

639
00:23:55,416 --> 00:23:56,958
and no one ever stops talking.

